videos.description: Alabama QB Jalen Hurts is sacked at his own 5-yard line in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Mississippi State defense sacks Hurts

videos.description: Bulldogs running back Aeris Williams runs through the Alabama defense on his way to an 11-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Mississippi State strikes first

videos.description: Crimson Tide WR Calvin Ridley evades multiple defenders on his way to a 63-yard gain.
videos.headline: Alabama's Ridley breaks defenders' ankles  for 63-yard gain

videos.description: Alabama's Jalen Hurts out runs the defense to the end zone, tying the game for the Tide.
videos.headline: Hurts keeps it himself for TD

videos.description: Bulldogs running back Aeris Williams pounds his way into the end zone for the second time in the first half.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Williams scores second TD

videos.description: Alabama QB Jalen Hurts finds a wide open Calvin Ridley who takes it 61 yards to the Mississippi State 1-yard line.
videos.headline: Ridley gashes Bulldogs defense for 61-yards

videos.description: Josh Jacobs bullies his way into the end zone for the Crimson Tide in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Alabama's Jacobs pushes his way in for TD

videos.description: Alabama head coach Nick Saban says that they need to be able to run the ball effectively, as well as stop the run defensively in the second half.
videos.headline: Saban wants to get the run game going in the second half

videos.description: Mississippi State head coach Dan Mullen says that his team just needs to keep playing well in the second half to beat Alabama.
videos.headline: Mullen: 'We've got to keep executing'

videos.description: Crimson Tide running back Damien Harris runs through the Bulldog defense for a 48-yard gain in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Alabama's Harris bursts for a 48-yard gain

videos.description: Bulldogs QB Nick Fitzgerald puts his shoulder down and pushes his way into the end zone giving Mississippi State the lead in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Fitzgerald drives his way into the end zone

videos.description: The Bulldogs defense knocks down Alabama quarterback Jalen Hurts' pass on third down forcing a punt.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's defense shuts down Jalen Hurts

videos.description: Damien Harris runs it in from 14 yards out to tie the game in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Alabama's Harris runs in for second TD

videos.description: Andy Pappanastos misses a 41-yard field goal attempt late in the fourth quarter leaving the game tied at 24.
videos.headline: Alabama's Pappanastos misses FG

videos.description: Jalen Hurts hits his wide receiver DeVonta Smith who takes it 26 yards and sends Alabama to a thrilling win.
videos.headline: Hurts to Smith for winning TD

videos.description: Alabama linebacker Kieth Holcombe tackles Mississippi State's Todd Reginald giving the Bulldogs one last Hail Mary attempt.
videos.headline: Alabama defense called for pass interference on Hail Mary

videos.description: Alabama head coach Nick Saban says that he is proud of how resilient his team was, beating out Mississippi State 31-24.
videos.headline: Saban: 'Really proud of our guys'

videos.description: Alabama QB Jalen Hurts says he told his team he was going to lead them to victory, and he did just that as the Crimson Tide held off the Bulldogs 31-24.
videos.headline: Hurts says halftime speech inspired team

videos.description: Jalen Hurts connects with DeVonta Smith to take the lead late and Mississippi State can't connect on the Hail Mary as Alabama survives.

videos.description: The Crimson Tide move to 10-0 as they run for three scores and 202 yards in a game they trailed late before a Jalen Hurts-DeVonta Smith touchdown connection with 0:25 remaining.
videos.headline: Alabama survives in Starkville

videos.description: Alabama finds a way to outlast Mississippi State and has No. 1 ranking sitting on the doorstep.
